  <h1 id="intro">Introduction to Memory Impairment</h1>
  <h5>Among the elderly, memory and other cognitive declines are common concerns. They may worry that learning new skills is taking longer than usual, or sometimes when they forget to pay their bills.</h5>
  <h5>In fact, aging is often associated with this mild forgetfulness and it is not a serious memory problem.</h5>
  <h5>However, when it is difficult for you to perform daily tasks like driving, using the phone, or getting home, you are likely to have serious memory or cognitive problems, and seeking medical attention is highly recommended. (<a href="https://www.nia.nih.gov/health/memory-forgetfulness-and-aging-whats-normal-and-whats-not#:~:text=Some%20older%20adults%20have%20a,and%20do%20their%20normal%20activities.">National Institute on Aging, 2020</a>).</h5>


