    <h1 id="risk">Risks & Causes of Memory Impairment</h1>
    <h5> Several risk factors have already been identified in the literature, such as:</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/Medizzy.png" alt=""> Medication Side Effects (some medications for anxiety, depression, seizure ...etc.)</h5>
    <h5> <img src="images/braininj.png" alt=""> Head Injury (concussions)</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/insomnia.png" alt=""> Lack od sleep (insomnia)</h5>
    <h5> <img src="images/vitamin.png" alt=""> Nutritional Deficiencies (B12, B6, B1, D, Folate vitamins deficiency)</h5>
    <h5> <img src="images/thyroid.png" alt=""> Thyroid Issues (decreased brain functionality due to hypothyroidism)</h5>
    <h5> <img src="images/neurone.png" alt=""> Neurodegenerative disorders (Dementia/Parkinson)</h5>




    <h1 id="complic">Complications of Memory Impairment</h1>
    <h5><img src="images/social.jpeg" alt=""> Social Isolation</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/miserable.png" alt=""> Quality of life Decline</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/depression.png" alt=""> Mental Health Impairment (Depression)</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/negative.png" alt=""> Negative Feeling & Behaviors</h5>



    <h1 id="prevent">Memory Impairment Prevention</h1>
    <h5><img src="images/learnskill.png" alt=""> Learn a new skill</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/diagnose.png" alt=""> Early detection of Memory impairment</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/list.png" alt=""> Make a to-do list and use memory tools (calendars and notes)</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/daily.png" alt=""> Follow a daily routine</h5>
    <h5><img src="images/interaction.png" alt=""> Spend time with friends and family </h5>
    <h5><img src="images/eatactive.png" alt=""> Exercise and eat nutrients-rich food</h5>
        <h5><img src="images/sleepwell.png" alt=""> Get enough Sleep</h5>

    <h1 id="how">When to see a doctor?</h1>
    <h5>Asking same questions over and over again.</h5>
    <h5>Having troubles following recipes or directions.</h5>
    <h5>Becoming more confused about time, people, and places.</h5>


